<TITLE> City mayoral hopefuls to appear in TV debates </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 1 (bdnews24.com) Upcoming televised debates between city corporation mayoral candidates will be held in the style of other well-known TV debates, said an election commissioner Saturday. Election commissioner M Sakhawat Hossain told bdnews24.com the debates would focus on the mayoral candidates' workplans as well as their election manifestoes. "The debates could be held at the central or local level. Voters will get a chance to put questions to the candidates and express their opinions in the BBC Sanglap-style." The Election Commission will finalise its strategy for the debates following a meeting with representatives from the BBC Sanglap production team, Channel i and Bangladesh Television on March 5, Sakhawat said. The commissioner said that the BBC Sanglap producers and Channel i both had experience in organising such events. "After the work strategy is finalised, other media houses may also come forward." On Feb 27, chief election commissioner ATM Shamsul Huda announced the EC was considering televised debates between candidates for the city corporation elections. The CEC said if the initiative was successful similar debates would be held prior to the Jatiya Sangsad elections. The EC is also set to announced the schedule for elections to Rajshahi, Khulna, Barisal and Sylhet city corporations in March, Huda said. bdnews24.
